# public/_redirects
#
# ─── NETLIFY-ONLY FILE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file is processed by Netlify at the CDN edge. Apache (cPanel,
# shared hosting) does NOT understand this format and will treat it as a
# file with no special meaning. If you are deploying to cPanel, DELETE
# dist/_redirects before uploading (the .htaccess in public/.htaccess
# handles everything for Apache). See DEPLOYMENT_CPANEL.md.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Rules are processed top-to-bottom and the FIRST match wins, so order
# matters: the more specific (API) rule MUST come before the catch-all
# SPA rule, otherwise the catch-all swallows the request and we get a
# 404 / index.html in place of the function response.

# Same-origin proxy for the Kimchi LLM API. This is the rule the
# `netlify.toml` redirect was supposed to provide, but on this site the
# `public/_redirects` file is processed with higher priority at the CDN
# edge, so we declare it here to be safe.
/api/kimchi/*  /.netlify/functions/kimchi/:splat  200

# Single-page-app fallback. Any request that is not a real static asset
# resolves to index.html so client-side routes (e.g. /projects/:id) work.
/*  /index.html  200
